## Hard Limits — Know These Before Scaling

| Limit | Free | Pro | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| Concurrent connections | 200 | 500 | Per PROJECT (not per user) |
| Events/second | 100 | 500 | Across all channels |
| Max channels per client | 100 | 100 | Per WebSocket connection |
| Message size | 1 MB | 1 MB | Hard limit — larger messages silently dropped |
| Postgres Changes joins per client | 2 | 10 | Separate limit for DB listeners |

### Error codes when limits hit
```
too_many_channels     — client has too many channels open
too_many_connections  — project hit concurrent connection limit
too_many_joins        — too many Postgres Changes listeners
rate_limited          — events/second exceeded
```

**Supabase CAN suspend your project for chronic limit violations.** They send a warning first.

