## Subscribe Status — Handle All States

```typescript
channel.subscribe((status, err) => {
  switch (status) {
    case 'SUBSCRIBED':
      // ✅ Connected and receiving events
      setConnectionState('connected')
      break

    case 'TIMED_OUT':
      // ⚠️ Connection attempt timed out — retry
      // Often caused by Node.js version incompatibility or network issues
      console.warn('Realtime timed out, retrying...')
      setConnectionState('connecting')
      setTimeout(() => channel.subscribe(), 2000)
      break

    case 'CHANNEL_ERROR':
      // ❌ Authorization failed — check RLS policies
      // If using private: true → check realtime.messages policies
      // If using postgres_changes → check table RLS + schema grants
      console.error('Channel error:', err?.message)
      setConnectionState('error')
      break

    case 'CLOSED':
      // Connection closed — may be intentional or network drop
      setConnectionState('disconnected')
      break
  }
})
```

